<br>
None of us has relished the attention this episode has gotten, nor do I think any of the parties involved believed what they did was ethically in the wrong.  The point is, though, that nothing can be changed unless we all learn from what has transpired.  And, I believe, many involved on all sides have learned a great deal so that chances of these parties being involved in this again will be greatly reduced.  (Will this type of event happen again over RF?...Heck, yeah, I can guarantee you it will...probably on the very next spawn..but I bet you won't see these 3 guilds snapping at each other over it. LOL) Actions, however rightly conceived, can have drastic side effects that none ever imagined, and this was probably one such instance where that was proven true.  <br>
